Thank you for using LegalZoom.

Based on standard requirements set by the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office (USPTO), it appears that your specimen may be incomplete.

Acceptable specimens for a series of creative works (i.e. DVDs, CDs, books, downloadable recordings) generally display the applied-for mark on at least two (2) different works; for example, two different CD covers or two different book covers displaying the same Trademark. Please note your specimen must also clearly reflect the specific product description on your application.

According to the USPTO, the title of a single creative work is not registrable on either the Principal or Supplemental Register. For more information regarding single creative works, please visit here.

Please reply to this email with appropriate specimens to be used on your application, preferably in .gif, .pdf, .jpeg or .jpg format. Alternately, you can send the specimen to us by mail. Our mailing address is:

